  "text": "First, we present the benchmarking of our baseline on three autonomous driving datasets. Table 3 presents benchmarking on Caltech [CITATION_1] dataset, Table 4 on CityPersons [CITATION_2] and Table 5 on ECP [CITATION_3] respectively. In the case of Caltech and CityPersons, our baseline without \"bells and whistles\" performs comparable to the existing state-of-the-art, which are tailored for pedestrian detection tasks. Its performance has a greater improvement compared to other methods with increasing dataset size. Its relative performance is worst on the smallest dataset (Caltech) and best on the largest dataset (EuroCityPersons).",
